(1, 'E62D03E551C1367C1AB0D4A0C99EF3CC', 'How this app works', 'LIVE', 1, 1, 'How this app works', 'how_this_app_works_1.jpg', 1, 'Welcome to the DK Readers app. The app provides a safe and self-contained bookstore packed with DK Readers to browse and buy. You can set up a bookshelf for each young reader in your home and fill it with the right DK Readers for your child, to enjoy over and over again. Here is a quick guide to getting the most from this app. \r\n\r\nAfter the welcome screen, you will be asked to create a parentâ€™s PIN number. This ensures your child cannot make purchases without your permission. Weâ€™ll ask for your e-mail address so if you forget your PIN we can send you a reminder. \r\n\r\nThe next step is creating a bookshelf for your child. Weâ€™ll ask for each childâ€™s name and reading level. You can adjust the level later on as your child makes progress. Get access to books directly from your bookshelf. Tap the â€œadd bookâ€ button and choose either the bookstore, or from titles your family has already purchased. \r\n\r\nThe DK Reader Bookstore contains a library of ebooks at five different reading levels to browse and buy. You can tap on a title to bring up a short summary about the ebook, and download a sample to browse for free. New ebooks will be added to the Bookstore every month. If you decide to purchase the ebook, you will be asked for your PIN to proceed. Itâ€™s that simple.\r\n\r\nNow itâ€™s over to your DK Reader. In the Bookstore, your child can browse through the ebooks with you and add titles to a wish list. When opening his or her bookshelf, your child can choose from a series of pictures to personalize the shelf. \r\n\r\nGet reading! Tap a book to open it. Your child can enable the read-aloud feature and set the volume, and choose whether or not to turn the pages. Mini-pages at the bottom of the screen show where your child is in the ebook. Finished? Click a button and let your parents know. Parents can access a page to see what their child has been reading, review purchases, reset PIN, and restore any purchases that may no longer be viewed. The DK Reader App is easy to use, and an easy way to get your child reading with confidence.\r\n\r\nFor questions or queries please contact customerservices@dk.com', 1, 'LIVE', '2013-11-12 10:27:03', '2014-02-24 09:59:22'),
(2, '5E2A2455FCDAEC8F8A166496A4C82C0D', 'About DK Readers', 'LIVE', 2, 2, 'About DK Readers', 'about_dk_readers_1.jpg', 1, 'DK Readers is a compelling, highly pictorial programme for beginning readers, designed in conjunction with leading literacy experts. Beautiful illustrations and superb full-colour photographs combine with engaging, easy-to-read stories to offer a fresh approach to each subject in the series. The five levels of DK Readers are aimed at different reading abilities, enabling you to choose the books that are exactly right for your child. Each DK Reader is designed to capture a childâ€™s interest while developing his or her reading skills, general knowledge, and love of reading. With DK Readers, children learn to read, then read to learn.', 1, 'LIVE', '2013-11-12 10:31:35', '2013-11-25 16:54:43'),
(3, '7FC0FC4AF190535A57FB753633441817', 'Reading levels', 'LIVE', 3, 1, 'Reading levels', 'reading_levels_1.jpg', 1, 'The five levels of DK Readers are created for different reading abilities, so that you can choose the books that are exactly right for your child. As his or her reading skills improve and grow, your child can move along the levels. No matter which level you select, you know DK Readers are the right reads for your child.\r\n\r\nPre-level 1, Learning to read\r\n* High-frequency words\r\n* Picture word strips, picture glossary, and simple index\r\n* Labels to introduce and reinforce vocabulary\r\n* High level of adult participation helpful\r\n\r\nLevel 1, Beginning to read\r\n* Simple sentences and limited vocabulary\r\n* Picture glossary and simple index\r\n* Adult participation helpful\r\n\r\nLevel 2, Beginning to read alone\r\n* Longer sentences and increased vocabulary\r\n* Information boxes full of extra fun facts\r\n* Simple index\r\n* Occasional adult participation helpful\r\n\r\nLevel 3, Reading alone\r\n* More complex sentence structure\r\n* Information boxes full of extra fun facts\r\n* Comprehensive index\r\n\r\nLevel 4, Proficient readers\r\n* Rich vocabulary and challenging sentence structure\r\n* Additional information and alphabetical glossary\r\n* Comprehensive index', 1, 'LIVE', '2013-11-12 10:35:20', '2013-11-25 16:55:20'),
