(9, '54417484B7258D67F49C48896D7DFFC8', 'Why reading with your child matters', 'LIVE', 4, 3, 'Why reading with your child matters', 'why_reading_with_your_child_matters_1.jpg', 1, 'Learning how to read is a key starting step for all learning. Helping children to become confident readers will help them succeed not just in all areas at school, but in life. As well as giving your child access to a whole world of information, reading for pleasure builds creative imagination, a sense of adventure, and enjoyment. Ebooks are so convenient â€“ you can access a whole library while you are out and about. If you want to raise a reader, be a reader. Share DK Readers with your child and give your child the gift of a lifetime love of reading.', 1, 'LIVE', '2013-11-12 10:48:58', '2013-11-25 16:56:01'),
(10, 'ECFECD02FC043AA495418E86C2B29FA1', 'Tips to support young readers', 'LIVE', 5, 2, 'Tips to support young readers', 'tips_to_support_young_readers_1.jpg', 1, 'For many children, reading is tricky, but adult participation can make learning both easier and more fun. So here are a few tips on how to use your DK Reader ebooks with your child.\r\n\r\nCheck out the content together before your child begins\r\nRead the descriptive text about the DK Reader in the bookstore. Download the free book sample and discuss the contents with your child to heighten interest. If there are unfamiliar or difficult words in the sample, work them out. Chat about the non-fiction reading features used in the book, such as headings and captions.\r\n\r\nSupport your child while reading the story\r\nLet your child read and scroll through the pages of the DK Reader. Where necessary, encourage your child to break a tricky word into syllables. Sound out each one and then flow them together. Ask your child to reread the sentence to check the meaning. Itâ€™s a great idea to encourage your child read out loud to you. When there is a question mark or exclamation mark, encourage your child to vary the voice while reading.\r\n\r\nPraise, share, chat\r\nTry and share a book together every day. Little and often is best. DK Readers are divided into manageable chapters for one reading session. Always encourage your child to have a go at reading difficult words. Praise any self-corrections and chat about the story when youâ€™ve finished. Itâ€™s ideal to read other books of different types and in different formats (digital and print) to your child just for enjoyment.', 1, 'LIVE', '2013-11-12 10:51:14', '2013-11-25 16:57:01'),
(11, '0D4B65F9456360BF899620EAC6BF7A10', 'Featured DK Readers', 'LIVE', 6, 1, 'Featured DK Readers', 'featured_dk_readers_1.jpg', 1, 'There are more than 180 titles in the DK Readers series and that number is growing each year. Each month, look for new titles across a range of levels and subjects in the DK Reader Bookstore. Weâ€™ll highlight the new titles in a banner so that they are easy to find. With so many age-appropriate stories, you are sure to find a DK Reader that is right for your favourite bookworm.', 1, 'LIVE', '2013-11-12 10:52:32', '2013-11-25 16:58:09'),
(12, 'F7793F4E422A575F43E51167B497038B', 'Free DK Readers', 'LIVE', 7, 2, 'Free DK Readers', 'free_dk_readers_1.jpg', 1, 'To help you build your childâ€™s DK Reader Bookshelf, we are delighted to offer a selection of five DK Readers, one at each level, for you to download for free. We hope you enjoy your free ebooks, and encourage you to read along with your child. A lifetime love of reading begins here.', 1, 'LIVE', '2013-11-12 10:53:30', '2013-11-25 16:58:57'),
(13, 'A3994C58129ACAD251433CD8424C2F96', 'About DK', 'LIVE', 8, 3, 'About DK', 'about_dk_1.jpg', 1, 'Established in 1974, DK creates best-selling, award-winning, and visually stunning information for adults and children, visit www.dk.com to find out more. From travel guides and activity books, through to food, history, gardening, and much more, DK makes ideas come to life.\r\n\r\nDK has established a worldwide reputation for its innovative nonfiction books in which the unrivaled clarity of the words and pictures come together to spectacular effect. DK content in all its forms is characterised by quality, expertise, and accessibility. DK is a brand that inspires trust and we pride ourselves in creating visual information with international appeal, working with companies worldwide who share our values and ethos.\r\n\r\nOur adult range spans from travel, including the award-winning Eyewitness Travel Guides to history, science, nature, sports, gardening, cookery, and parenting. We also publish an extensive children''s catalogue that showcases a fantastic store of knowledge for children, toddlers, and babies. Covering topics from history and the human body to animals and activities, DK children''s books combine outstanding information with magical illustration and design.\r\n\r\nWe work closely with authors who are experts in their field, with authoritative institutions like the Royal Horticultural Society and the Smithsonian, as well as with well-known brands such as Star Wars and the LEGO Group, to produce world-class books and products. \r\n\r\nDK has offices in Delhi, London, Melbourne, Munich, New York, and Toronto.', 1, 'LIVE', '2013-11-12 10:56:00', '2013-11-25 16:59:22'),
